<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp125011360">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp171382272">
<p id="fs-idp156839632">&#8220;Thermite&#8221; reactions have been used for welding metal parts such as railway rails and in metal refining. One such thermite reaction is <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Fe</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mtext>O</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext>Al</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo stretchy="false">&#10230;</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msub><mrow><mtext>Al</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mtext>O</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext>Fe</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Fe</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mtext>O</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext>Al</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo stretchy="false">&#10230;</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msub><mrow><mtext>Al</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mtext>O</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext>Fe</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math>
Is the reaction spontaneous at room temperature under standard conditions? During the reaction, the surroundings absorb 851.8 kJ/mol of heat.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp175070256">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp169049488">
