</section>
<div data-type="glossary"><h3 data-type="glossary-title">Glossary</h3>
<dl id="fs-idp194754048">
<dt>second law of thermodynamics</dt>
<dd id="fs-idp194754688">all spontaneous processes involve an increase in the entropy of the universe</dd>
</dl>
<dl id="fs-idp170415152">
<dt>standard entropy (<em data-effect="italics">S</em>&#176;)</dt>
<dd id="fs-idp170416304">entropy for one mole of a substance at 1 bar pressure; tabulated values are usually determined at 298.15 K</dd>
</dl>
<dl id="fs-idp85418944">
<dt>standard entropy change (&#916;<em data-effect="italics">S</em>&#176;)</dt>
<dd id="fs-idp85420096">change in entropy for a reaction calculated using the standard entropies</dd>
</dl>
<dl id="fs-idp90512720">
<dt>third law of thermodynamics</dt>
<dd id="fs-idp90513360">entropy of a perfect crystal at absolute zero (0 K) is zero</dd>
</dl>
</div></body>

